snippet.title: 48 HOURS IN PARIS ft. Secret Bars, Bakeries & Cheese - Our alternative guide.
snippet.description:
This is a big one for us. We went to Paris for 48 hours and had a very, very good time. It’s a sweet 16 minutes long and we think it’s our favourite one yet.   

Thank you to everybody who recommended places for to visit in this episode. If you like it then please let us know as we’ve done things a little differently to before. 

If you’re liking the music then BIG SHOUT OUT TO THE TEAM FROM BROTHER MUSIC (https://brotherfilmco.com/music). They've just launched a new music service which we’re using for the first time in this episode. We’re all about working with local creatives and we’re very chuffed to work with Brother on the music in the future.

Next up, major shout out to our editor Rob who took a load of footage and managed to knock this into shape. 

We were also thinking it may be useful to start doing little city guides on Google Maps with our favourite places on. Let us know in the comments if you think these would be useful and where you would want one for. 

Just a note on the Hoxton - we didn't get paid to stay there. We really did love it. 

New to TOPJAW? Then Hiiiiiiiii! We’re Jesse & Will, a presenter and filmmaker duo based in London but spend our time travelling and filming fantastic things to eat, do, and see all over the world. 

You can follow us on Instagram: 
https://www.instagram.com/topjaw/

And Facebook: 
https://www.facebook.com/topjawfilms/ 

We know that you guys are interested in the equipment we use to make these films, so here it is: 
- Will’s camera in this video is a RED FS7
- And we use Canon L Series Lenses - 28mm, 50mm, 85mm, 100mm

Like our films but think they could be better? We’re always on the lookout for editors / producers / photographers / camera guys and girls who want to work with us. Please just send examples of your work to: hello@topjaw.co.uk

Next up - we’re in Bangkok for 48 Hours!!!

Big love, 

Jesse & Will x

comments.textDisplay:
Thank you so much for showing the beautiful secret side of Paris. Everybody only knows the Eiffel Tower or the Champs Elysees & the Louvre and even though this is something you have to absolutely do if you come to Paris, there are also so many wonderful & unique places to know Paris in a specific way & to tell everyone about this secret other side. I'm really proud to be a French girl thanks to our culture, our food & especially thanks to our unique way to develop our specific taste with the decoration by example & made every places & moments unforgettable. We also love to develop every culture that are living in Paris like the Asian one, the Indian one or the Arabic one & put them into some wonderful restaurants or markets. This is really beautiful.
By the way, you speaks so well & your video was an amazing way to show our capital. You were filming this short trip in a really good way & I really loved how you put everything together.
Glad to have find you on my trip to YouTube. A really lively recommendation.
Good luck for your next project & thank you very much 😉

comments.textDisplay: Hi! This was fun to watch. Next time you go, check out La Sainte Chapelle, it's close to Notre-Dame, older, virtually unknown and so stunningly beautiful! For a taste of French palaces without going to Versailles, visit the Palais Garnier, the opera house, they always have costumes on display. Also, going to a jazz club is a must, most of them are on the Rue des Lombards, the one I know is called the Duc des Lombards.
